<item>
            <title>[JAMES-2950] Username should not accept some special characters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JAMES-2950</link>
                <project id="10411" key="JAMES">James Server</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Able to create username with some special characters that should be restricted, such as:&#160; space and &lt;tt&gt;&quot;(),:;&amp;lt;&amp;gt;@[]&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should for more safety and reduce complexity not allow the use of those for the username (more specifically, the local-part of the user address)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
