                            <comment id="16963810" author="rcordier" created="Thu, 31 Oct 2019 09:43:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;PR: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/linagora/james-project/pull/2809&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/linagora/james-project/pull/2809&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16971271" author="btellier" created="Mon, 11 Nov 2019 02:08:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/linagora/james-project/pull/2841&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/linagora/james-project/pull/2841&lt;/a&gt; proposed a rewritte of RRT regex tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;RRT regex was trying to fit a &apos;regex&apos; in a string representing a Username. Tests were actively testing this bug, causing the tests to be meaningless.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This PR:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Rewrite the test in order not to rely exclusively on error buggy handling, which also makes the feature easier to understand.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Did fix the buggy error handling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
